371
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:49,577
Thank you!

372
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:54,330
[RUTH] Normal, Illinois is a small town.

373
00:22:54,331 --> 00:22:56,749
Jeff had never seen those guys before

374
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:59,295
and he never saw them again.

375
00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:17,187
[DR. KATINE] Double vision.
Can't keep his balance.

376
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:20,064
Does he got headaches or dizziness?

377
00:23:20,065 --> 00:23:22,067
Yeah... all of that.

378
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:31,076
[RUTH] Uh... we're looking
for a patient Eric Elliott.

379
00:23:35,623 --> 00:23:37,081
[RUTH] Oh! Jeff!

380
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:38,584
[JEN] Dad.

381
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:41,794
Hi.

382
00:23:41,795 --> 00:23:42,378
Hi.

383
00:23:42,379 --> 00:23:46,090
I'm Keith Kattner. I'm a
neurosurgeon on staff here.

384
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:50,054
The MRI has detected a tumor
at the base of his skull.

385
00:23:52,431 --> 00:23:54,015
And it's a big one.

386
00:23:54,016 --> 00:23:56,225
[DR.KATTNER] It's pressing up against his

387
00:23:56,226 --> 00:23:58,102
medulla and optic nerve,

388
00:23:58,103 --> 00:23:59,604
which explains the double vision.

389
00:23:59,605 --> 00:24:00,688
[JEFF] Is it malignant?

390
00:24:00,689 --> 00:24:03,066
<i>[DEL KATTNER] 1 won't. know
for sure uni.“ 1 biopsy it,</i>

391
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:04,734
but it's definitely got to come out.

392
00:24:04,735 --> 00:24:06,027
Let's get it out.

393
00:24:06,028 --> 00:24:09,030
But it's important that you
know the facts up front.

394
00:24:09,031 --> 00:24:11,199
There are a lot of risks associated

395
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,575
with operating on the brain.

396
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:15,244
Can you be specific please?

397
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:18,706
[DR. KATTNER] There is a chance
that it could send Eric into

398
00:24:18,707 --> 00:24:20,541
a severe coma and leave him

399
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:23,002
neurologically impaired for life.

400
00:24:23,003 --> 00:24:24,672
There is that chance.

401
00:24:25,547 --> 00:24:28,174
What are the chances?

402
00:24:28,175 --> 00:24:30,551
Thirty percent statistically.

403
00:24:30,552 --> 00:24:32,720
What if we don't operate?

404
00:24:32,721 --> 00:24:35,723
[DR. KATTNER] The tumor is far
along and it's aggressive.

405
00:24:35,724 --> 00:24:39,687
It will kill him one hundred percent.

406
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:42,523
[Ruth sobs]

407
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:50,030
[monitor beeps]

408
00:24:56,412 --> 00:24:58,706
[Hoovey utters something]

409
00:25:02,292 --> 00:25:05,337
[HOOVEY] It's a brain tumor isn't it?

410
00:25:08,048 --> 00:25:09,633
[JEFF] Yep.

411
00:25:11,385 --> 00:25:13,094
It's actually kind of a relief.

412
00:25:13,095 --> 00:25:15,722
Now I know why I was playing so bad.

413
00:25:15,723 --> 00:25:18,058
You weren't playing bad.

414
00:25:19,685 --> 00:25:22,229
Don't worry Dad.

415
00:25:22,563 --> 00:25:26,525
If I... you know...

416
00:25:26,984 --> 00:25:29,528
I know where I'm going.

417
00:25:30,404 --> 00:25:32,531
[Jeff starts to cry]

418
00:25:34,992 --> 00:25:37,411
We're going to get through this.

419
00:25:41,206 --> 00:25:45,168
[RUTH] It is the one thing
every parent fears the most.

420
00:25:45,169 --> 00:25:47,378
Something happening to our child.

421
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:50,173
Something we are powerless to stop.

422
00:25:50,174 --> 00:25:53,927
And there is nothing you can do...
but pray.

423
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:04,521
[JEN] Dad...

424
00:26:05,731 --> 00:26:07,482
How bad is it?

425
00:26:07,483 --> 00:26:09,233
I mean like...

426
00:26:09,234 --> 00:26:12,529
Could he... die?

427
00:26:14,031 --> 00:26:16,033
That's not going to happen.

428
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,623
Is that up to you?

429
00:26:35,219 --> 00:26:38,430
[DR. KATTNER] That's the
problem with the medulla...

430
00:26:38,722 --> 00:26:40,306
[UNKNOWN] Vitals are stable.

431
00:26:40,307 --> 00:26:43,726
[DR. KATTNER] And that can...
can be a problem.

432
00:26:43,727 --> 00:26:46,605
[electric shears]

433
00:26:50,234 --> 00:26:51,692
[VOICES ECHOING]

434
00:26:51,693 --> 00:26:52,527
[DR. KATTNER] Alright... very nice.

435
00:26:52,528 --> 00:26:55,572
Sponge. Okay... Good.

436
00:26:59,118 --> 00:27:01,453
Right there.

437
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:12,589
[dramatic music]

438
00:27:38,615 --> 00:27:40,741
[DR. KATTNER] It was benign and we got it.

439
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:42,243
He's out of the woods.

440
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:43,202
Can we see him?

441
00:27:43,203 --> 00:27:44,620
[DR. KATTNER] Of course.
He's asleep right now,

442
00:27:44,621 --> 00:27:47,039
but we'll wake him in about an hour.

443
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:49,458
Uh... there was a slight complication.

444
00:27:49,459 --> 00:27:52,712
I had to remove a fairly
large section of bone

445
00:27:52,713 --> 00:27:55,173
