630
00:39:27,407 --> 00:39:30,118
We need a new septic tank.

631
00:39:31,661 --> 00:39:34,246
How much does that cost?

632
00:39:34,247 --> 00:39:37,333
More than we have, but
what's new about that?

633
00:39:38,668 --> 00:39:40,544
How's your day look?

634
00:39:40,545 --> 00:39:43,630
I've got some intellectually
stimulating brush and stump

635
00:39:43,631 --> 00:39:46,049
removal over at the Long's farm.

636
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:48,051
Hundred bucks as long as my back holds out,

637
00:39:48,052 --> 00:39:50,470
and uh... them I'm going
to deliver me some pizzas,

638
00:39:50,471 --> 00:39:54,558
and then uh... I'm going to help
Fred Hollander clean the bank.

639
00:39:54,559 --> 00:39:56,059
And then you're back on shift.

640
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:57,561
[JEFF] Living the dream baby.

641
00:39:57,562 --> 00:39:59,355
Living the dream.

642
00:40:00,231 --> 00:40:04,193
It's still my dream. And
you're still my Superman.

643
00:40:06,738 --> 00:40:08,238
Can we sell the place?

644
00:40:08,239 --> 00:40:09,991
Not for what we owe them.

645
00:40:11,743 --> 00:40:13,452
Then I have to go back to work.

646
00:40:13,453 --> 00:40:16,204
Where? Half this town is looking for a job.

647
00:40:16,205 --> 00:40:18,040
Well I can deliver pizzas.

648
00:40:18,041 --> 00:40:20,667
I can... mow lawns and...

649
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:23,128
Don't worry baby, I got this.

650
00:40:23,129 --> 00:40:24,212
Nothings more important than what you're

651
00:40:24,213 --> 00:40:25,714
doing here right now any way, so...

652
00:40:25,715 --> 00:40:27,382
What am I doing?

653
00:40:27,383 --> 00:40:29,218
Holding us together.

654
00:40:31,512 --> 00:40:32,721
I gotta go.

655
00:40:32,722 --> 00:40:34,182
Hey"-

656
00:40:34,724 --> 00:40:38,686
I love you. We're gonna get through this.

657
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:45,693
[door closes]

658
00:40:46,945 --> 00:40:49,529
{music}

659
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:50,614
[squeaking shoes and
plays being called out]

660
00:40:50,615 --> 00:40:52,450
Let's go D!

661
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:56,912
[whistle]

662
00:40:56,913 --> 00:40:57,996
<i>No no!</i>

663
00:40:57,997 --> 00:41:00,749
To the left... the ball has to
go to the center post first.

664
00:41:00,750 --> 00:41:01,667
He wasn't there!

665
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:03,836
Yet. You gotta let him set up!

666
00:41:05,046 --> 00:41:06,839
[COACH WILSON] Alright...
Let's do it again!

667
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:17,475
[whistle]

668
00:41:20,061 --> 00:41:20,978
Coach!

669
00:41:20,979 --> 00:41:21,895
[COACH WILSON] Yeah?

670
00:41:21,896 --> 00:41:23,564
[HOOVEY] Can I?

671
00:41:23,815 --> 00:41:25,274
Come on.

672
00:41:28,861 --> 00:41:32,406
It's like a wheel...
that turns to the left.

673
00:41:32,407 --> 00:41:35,826
If you got to one side
like that, it's lopsided.

674
00:41:35,827 --> 00:41:38,745
You'll get trapped by the
double team every single time.

675
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:40,623
What are you talking about?

676
00:41:42,542 --> 00:41:44,710
You've got a hole at the top of the key.

677
00:41:44,711 --> 00:41:48,046
Wait for the first screen... then go left.

678
00:41:48,047 --> 00:41:51,009
Yeah... yeah sure thing coach.

679
00:41:52,010 --> 00:41:53,386
Donovan.

680
00:41:54,762 --> 00:41:56,973
He's absolutely right.

681
00:41:57,557 --> 00:41:59,349
But that's not how we did it at my school.

682
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:01,476
Well that's the way we do it here.

683
00:42:01,477 --> 00:42:02,686
Maybe you should think about that while

684
00:42:02,687 --> 00:42:04,396
you run twenty laps for us!

685
00:42:04,397 --> 00:42:06,024
NOW!

686
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:28,545
[MIKE] The equity you have
in your farm doesn't even

687
00:42:28,546 --> 00:42:32,007
come close to what you
owe in medical bills.

688
00:42:32,008 --> 00:42:34,051
They just keep coming.

689
00:42:34,052 --> 00:42:35,552
We're working it out...

690
00:42:35,553 --> 00:42:37,679
It's just temporary.

691
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,640
[RUTH] We just need a bridge loan.

692
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:43,436
Mike you know us. We're lifers around here.

693
00:42:43,770 --> 00:42:45,812
