money for middle level salary.

697
00:42:55,948 --> 00:42:59,535
Honestly... no.

698
00:43:36,739 --> 00:43:38,782
[JEFF] I guess it's been
a little while right?

699
00:43:38,783 --> 00:43:40,660
[HOOVEY] Yeah.

700
00:43:42,912 --> 00:43:44,412
[HOOVEY] It's about time.

701
00:43:44,413 --> 00:43:45,872
[JEFF] Just keep your eyes
focused straight ahead,

702
00:43:45,873 --> 00:43:48,835
Blazer will get you there.
She knows the way.

703
00:43:50,837 --> 00:43:52,379
[reeling in sound]

704
00:43:52,380 --> 00:43:53,881
[HOOVEY] Hey dad...

705
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:56,800
What did you want to be
when you were my age?

706
00:43:56,801 --> 00:43:58,678
[JEFF] Married to your mom.

707
00:43:59,971 --> 00:44:01,555
Come on.

708
00:44:01,556 --> 00:44:03,890
I did... I wanted to be
quarterback of the Bears,

709
00:44:03,891 --> 00:44:06,853
and married to your mom and
own a sixty foot bass boat.

710
00:44:07,436 --> 00:44:08,854
[JEFF] You know your mom and me are proud

711
00:44:08,855 --> 00:44:11,606
that you decided to help
the team out by coaching.

712
00:44:11,607 --> 00:44:13,900
[HOOVEY] Yeah... but I can't
wait to get out there

713
00:44:13,901 --> 00:44:15,819
and start playing again Dad.

714
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:17,363
[JEFF] Well...

715
00:44:18,906 --> 00:44:22,368
The truth is, you can't
play basketball anymore.

716
00:44:22,910 --> 00:44:24,954
One good shot to the head could kill you.

717
00:44:26,914 --> 00:44:28,456
That's official?

718
00:44:28,457 --> 00:44:29,834
Yeah.

719
00:44:30,543 --> 00:44:34,505
[HOOVEY] And you're just now...
telling me because...

720
00:44:37,049 --> 00:44:41,012
{music}

721
00:45:42,949 --> 00:45:44,909
How ya doing', Coach?

722
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:54,834
I... don't think I can do this anymore.

723
00:45:54,835 --> 00:45:58,046
It's killing me.

724
00:45:58,047 --> 00:46:00,548
Why is this happening, Coach?

725
00:46:00,549 --> 00:46:02,426
What did I do wrong?

726
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:09,976
[COACH WILSON] So, uh... the
good Lord was having a talk with

727
00:46:10,977 --> 00:46:13,561
the Devil one day.

728
00:46:13,562 --> 00:46:15,897
Bragging on his man Job.

729
00:46:15,898 --> 00:46:18,775
"See how he loves me? Serves me?"

730
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:20,735
"Well," said the Devil. "Why wouldn't he?

731
00:46:20,736 --> 00:46:22,779
You give him everything. [scoffs]

732
00:46:22,780 --> 00:46:26,742
Money, power... land, children.

733
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:30,578
Let me take it away from him, and watch him

734
00:46:30,579 --> 00:46:32,539
curse you to your face."

735
00:46:32,540 --> 00:46:35,500
And God said, "Oh, okay."

736
00:46:35,501 --> 00:46:38,962
So the Devil does. He takes everything.

737
00:46:38,963 --> 00:46:43,049
Leaves old Job with nothing,
sitting in the dirt,

738
00:46:43,050 --> 00:46:44,759
covered with boils.

739
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:46,469
[chuckles]

740
00:46:46,470 --> 00:46:50,557
Finally old Job had had enough.

741
00:46:50,558 --> 00:46:52,435
What do you reckon he said?

742
00:46:54,312 --> 00:46:57,898
"It was... all His to begin with."

743
00:47:00,860 --> 00:47:03,570
He didn't do anything wrong.

744
00:47:03,571 --> 00:47:05,614
Neither did you.

745
00:47:11,412 --> 00:47:12,621
[horse snorts]

746
00:47:20,504 --> 00:47:21,672
[horse snorts]

747
00:47:23,591 --> 00:47:26,051
[metal chain clanks, fence creaks open]

748
00:47:26,052 --> 00:47:27,720
Woah.

749
00:47:30,973 --> 00:47:32,933
[fence clangs shut]

750
00:47:46,906 --> 00:47:49,407
